org.apache.flex.abc.models

Interface TreeModelVisitor<T>


  • public interface TreeModelVisitor<T>
    A TreeModelVisitor translates stack-oriented operations into a operation/operands view of an ABC method body.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  TreeModelVisitor.IMergePoint<T>
      IMergePoint models a point where several predecessors' values combine in the dataflow graph.

          Collection<T> operands)
        Translate an Instruction and its operands into an intermediate form.
        Parameters:
        insn - - the Instruction that encoded this operation.
        operands - - the Instruction's operands, usually from the ABC value stack.
        Returns:

      • valueStackUnderflow

        T valueStackUnderflow(Instruction insn,
                    int count)
        Recover from a value stack underflow condition.
        Parameters:
        insn - - the Instruction that attempted to encode this operation.
        count - - the number of stack values required.
        Returns:
        a representation of the recovery action; returning some type of "bottom value" is recommended.

      • scopeStackUnderflow

        T scopeStackUnderflow(Instruction insn,
                    int count)
        Recover from a scope stack underflow condition.
        Parameters:
        insn - - the Instruction that attempted to encode this operation.
        count - - the number of scope stack values required.
        Returns:
        a representation of the recovery action; returning some type of "bottom value" is recommended.
